# Styling Guidelines

## Tailwind CSS v4

### Configuration

- Tailwind CSS v4 with PostCSS ([postcss.config.mjs](mdc:postcss.config.mjs))
- Global styles in [app/globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css)
- CSS variables enabled for theming
- Base color: neutral

### Utility-First Approach

Use Tailwind utility classes for all styling:

```tsx
<div className="flex items-center justify-between p-4 bg-background">
  <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold">Title</h1>
</div>
```

### Class Merging

Use the `cn` utility from [lib/utils.ts](mdc:lib/utils.ts) for conditional classes:

```typescript
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

export function Component({ className, variant }: Props) {
  return (
    <div
      className={cn(
        "base-classes",
        variant === "large" && "text-lg",
        className
      )}
    >
      Content
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Theming & Dark Mode

### Dark Mode Support

- Uses `next-themes` package
- Theme provider in [components/theme-provider.tsx](mdc:components/theme-provider.tsx)
- CSS variables for colors (automatically switch in dark mode)

### Using Theme Colors

Use semantic color variables:

```tsx
<div className="bg-background text-foreground">
  <p className="text-muted-foreground">Secondary text</p>
  <div className="border border-border">Card</div>
</div>
```

### Available Color Variables

- `background` / `foreground`
- `card` / `card-foreground`
- `popover` / `popover-foreground`
- `primary` / `primary-foreground`
- `secondary` / `secondary-foreground`
- `muted` / `muted-foreground`
- `accent` / `accent-foreground`
- `destructive` / `destructive-foreground`
- `border`, `input`, `ring`

## Responsive Design

Use Tailwind responsive prefixes:

```tsx
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
  {/* Responsive grid */}
</div>
```

## Animations

- Use `tailwindcss-animate` for Tailwind animations
- Motion (Framer Motion) for complex animations
- Keep animations performant (use transform/opacity)

## Typography

Use consistent spacing and sizing:

```tsx
<h1 className="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">
<h2 className="text-3xl font-semibold">
<h3 className="text-2xl font-semibold">
<p className="text-base text-muted-foreground">
```

## Layout Patterns

- Use `flex` and `grid` for layouts
- Prefer `gap` over margin for spacing
- Use consistent padding: `p-4`, `p-6`, `p-8`
- Container widths: `max-w-7xl`, `mx-auto`
